condition.narrative: Finance Agreement :Schedule 2 - Section I Implementation, Institutional and Other Undertakings - F | Description :Every monththroughout Project implementation, Borrower shall undertake water flow measurements in the Alaknanda river | Frequency :Monthly

Finance Agreement :Schedule 2 - Section II (B) Financial Management,.., Financial Ratios - 5(a) | Description :Borrower shall takeall necessary steps to maintain its accounts receivable at a level not exceeding an amount equivalent to its billings for energygeneration for the preceding three (3) months | Frequency :Quarterly

Finance Agreement :Schedule 2 - Section II (B) Financial Management,.., Financial Ratios - 5(b) | Description :Borrower shallfurnish to the Bank, not later than December 31 of each year, its ten-year financial projections, including its investment programand financing plan throughout project implementation | Frequency :Yearly

Finance Agreement :Schedule 2 - Section II (B) Financial Management,.., Financial Ratios - 6(a) | Description :Except as the Bankshall otherwise agree, the Borrower shall not incur any debt, if after the incurrence of such debt the ratio of debt to equity ofthe Borrower shall be greater than four to one (4 to 1) | Frequency :CONTINUOUS

Finance Agreement: Schedule 2 - Section I Implementation, Institutional and Other Undertakings - H | Description: Borrower shallcarry out: (a) study to be completed by December 31, 2012, to assess the effectiveness of RAP implementation; and (b)a study to becompleted by January 31, 2017, to assess project impact on the living standards of PAPs and shall take timely and appropriatemeasures satisfactory to the Bank to address any issues or deficiencies | Due Date:31-Jan-2017

Finance Agreement:Schedule 2 - Section I Implementation, Institutional and Other Undertakings - G | Description: Borrower shallcarry out a study aimed at enhancing the Borrower's adaptive management capacity for implementation of minimum flow requirementsand mitigation impacts on aquatic ecology and wildlife in the stretch of the Alaknanda River under the project | Due Date:31-July2017
